{"session_id":"svc-1778198228351919139","seq":0,"type":"session.start","ts":"2026-05-07T23:57:10.366451601Z","data":{"provider":"","model":"sonnet","sticky":{"key_present":true,"assignment":"not_applicable","bonus":0},"utilization":{"observed_at":"0001-01-01T00:00:00Z"},"resolved_harness":"claude","harness_source":"auto_route","resolved_model":"sonnet","work_dir":"/var/tmp/ddx-exec-wt/.execute-bead-wt-ddx-60ed4dc9-20260507T235704-47853826","max_iterations":0,"prompt":"\u003cexecute-bead\u003e\n  \u003cinstructions\u003e\nYou are executing one bead inside an isolated DDx execution worktree. The bead\u0026#39;s \u0026lt;description\u0026gt; and \u0026lt;acceptance\u0026gt; are the completion contract — every AC must be provably satisfied by a specific code, test, or file you can point to after your commit.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## Step 0: size check\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;The bead is too big when any of these holds:\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;- More than ~6 ACs spanning unrelated subsystems.\u0026#xA;- AC mixes design, implementation, integration tests, and docs as separate top-level deliverables.\u0026#xA;- Description names multiple feature-sized sub-pieces.\u0026#xA;- More than ~500 lines across more than ~5 files in unrelated packages.\u0026#xA;- If the bead description exceeds 8000 bytes, treat Step 0 as a split-first pass and favor child-bead scoping before implementation.\u0026#xA;- Auto-decomposition is capped at depth 2: root beads may split once, decomposed children may split once more, and third-level splits must be rejected with an explanation.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;If too big, decompose — do not attempt the work:\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;1. `ddx bead create` for each child slice (focused title, description, AC; copy parent\u0026#39;s labels and spec-id).\u0026#xA;2. `ddx bead dep add \u0026lt;child-id\u0026gt; \u0026lt;parent-id\u0026gt;` to record edges.\u0026#xA;3. `ddx bead update \u0026lt;parent-id\u0026gt; --notes \u0026#39;decomposed into \u0026lt;child-ids\u0026gt;\u0026#39;` so the decomposition is visible.\u0026#xA;4. Write `.ddx/executions/20260507T235704-47853826/no_changes_rationale.txt` listing each child ID and slice, then stop.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;A clean decomposition is a successful attempt. Do not mix partial implementation with decomposition.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## How to work\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;- Read first. If the bead names files, specs, or prior beads, read them before editing — do not guess.\u0026#xA;- Cross-reference each AC against concrete evidence (test name, file path, function) before committing. If you cannot point at it, it is not done.\u0026#xA;- Run the project\u0026#39;s test and lint commands before committing. **Do not commit red code** — fix failures first.\u0026#xA;- Stage with `git add \u0026lt;specific-paths\u0026gt;`; never `git add -A` (the worktree may have unrelated WIP).\u0026#xA;- Commit exactly once when green; conventional-commit subject ending with `[\u0026lt;bead-id\u0026gt;]`. Stop after the commit.\u0026#xA;- Do not modify files outside the bead\u0026#39;s scope.\u0026#xA;- If you cannot finish, write `.ddx/executions/20260507T235704-47853826/no_changes_rationale.txt` (what is done, what blocks, what a follow-up needs) before exiting. No commit and no rationale ⇒ DDx records `no_evidence_produced`. A well-justified no_changes beats a bad commit.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## no_changes contract\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;If you write `.ddx/executions/20260507T235704-47853826/no_changes_rationale.txt`, it MUST carry one of:\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;- `verification_command: \u0026lt;one-line shell command\u0026gt;` — the loop runs it (cwd = project root, 60s); exit 0 closes the bead, non-zero rejects.\u0026#xA;- `status: needs_investigation` + `reason: \u0026lt;why\u0026gt;` — bead stays open for triage.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;Bare rationales (\u0026#34;nothing to do\u0026#34;) are rejected.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## Reports\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;Freestanding artifacts (investigation reports, findings docs) go under `.ddx/executions/20260507T235704-47853826/` (the per-attempt evidence directory under `.ddx/executions/`). **Never write reports to `/tmp` or any path outside the repository** — out-of-repo paths are invisible to the post-merge reviewer and cause BLOCK on missing evidence. If the bead names a specific in-repo path, use it; else default to `.ddx/executions/20260507T235704-47853826/\u0026lt;short-name\u0026gt;.md`. Stage and commit the report alongside code.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## Bead overrides project defaults\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;The bead description and AC override CLAUDE.md, AGENTS.md, and conservative project defaults (YAGNI, DOWITYTD, no-docs-unless-asked) in this worktree — write whatever the bead asks for.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## Review gate\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;- The review is a gate, not an escape hatch — meet every AC in this pass.\u0026#xA;- Address every BLOCKING `\u0026lt;review-findings\u0026gt;` item; do not declare `no_changes` with blocking findings open.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## Constraints\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;- Work only inside this execution worktree.\u0026#xA;- Keep `.ddx/executions/` intact — DDx uses it as execution evidence.\u0026#xA;- **Never run `ddx init`** — the workspace is initialized; running it corrupts the bead queue.\u0026#xA;- Do not modify files outside the bead\u0026#39;s named scope.\u0026#xA;- Do not rewrite CLAUDE.md, AGENTS.md, or other project-instructions files unless the bead asks.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## When the work is done\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;After the commit succeeds and every AC is verified, stop. Return control to the orchestrator — do not keep exploring or testing.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## Decomposition depth cap\u0026#xA;This bead is already at decomposition depth 2. Do not create another child layer; if it is still too large, reject the split with a short explanation and write no_changes_rationale.txt instead.\u0026#xA;\n  \u003c/instructions\u003e\n  \u003cbead id=\"ddx-60ed4dc9\"\u003e\n    \u003ctitle\u003eagent: preserve and migrate readiness result schema compatibility\u003c/title\u003e\n    \u003cdescription\u003e\nPROBLEM\u0026#xA;A new readiness skill contract could return JSON that the current Go intake decoder rejects, or legacy `MODE: intake` responses could break while migrating to readiness terminology.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;ROOT CAUSE WITH FILE:LINE\u0026#xA;- `cli/internal/agent/preclaim_intake.go:5-23` defines the current outcome shape around `actionable_atomic`, `actionable_but_rewritten`, `too_large_decomposed`, `ambiguous_needs_human`, and `intake_error`.\u0026#xA;- `cli/internal/agent/preclaim_intake_hook.go:111-134` decodes and validates one current intake schema.\u0026#xA;- `cli/internal/agent/preclaim_intake_hook_test.go:158` asserts `MODE: intake`, but no test covers canonical readiness JSON compatibility.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;PROPOSED FIX\u0026#xA;Add compatibility parsing so current `MODE: intake` responses still work while canonical readiness responses decode into the same decision model. Preserve prompt-source/event compatibility unless a spec-approved migration requires an explicit change.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;NON-SCOPE\u0026#xA;Do not rename user-facing output or implement failure taxonomy classification beyond parser mapping.\n    \u003c/description\u003e\n    \u003cacceptance\u003e\n1. Current intake JSON continues to decode.\u0026#xA;2. Canonical readiness JSON decodes into the same pre-claim decision model.\u0026#xA;3. Unknown readiness reason codes fail with actionable parser errors.\u0026#xA;4. `system_unready` maps to fail-open/skip behavior according to ADR-023/FEAT-010 policy.\u0026#xA;5. Prompt-source compatibility is preserved for existing tests/events.\u0026#xA;6. Unit tests `TestPreClaimReadiness_DecodesLegacyIntakeJSON` and `TestPreClaimReadiness_DecodesCanonicalReadinessJSON` cover both schemas.\u0026#xA;7. Unit test `TestPreClaimReadiness_UnknownReasonActionableError` covers unknown reason handling.\u0026#xA;8. `cd cli \u0026amp;\u0026amp; go test ./internal/agent/... -run \u0026#34;TestPreClaim(Readiness|Intake)|TestIntake\u0026#34; -count=1` passes.\u0026#xA;9. `lefthook run pre-commit` passes.\n    \u003c/acceptance\u003e\n    \u003clabels\u003ephase:2, area:agent, area:skills, kind:feature, reliability, bead-quality, adr:023, spec:FEAT-010\u003c/labels\u003e\n    \u003cmetadata parent=\"ddx-a9d130d0\" spec-id=\"ADR-023\" base-rev=\"b612b11eb8862a1382981b90852b9c6de68cb4c2\" bundle=\".ddx/executions/20260507T235704-47853826\"/\u003e\n  \u003c/bead\u003e\n  \u003cgoverning\u003e\n    \u003cref id=\"ADR-023\" path=\"docs/helix/02-design/adr/ADR-023-bead-lifecycle-quality-policy.md\"\u003eADR-023: Bead Lifecycle Quality Policy\u003c/ref\u003e\n  \u003c/governing\u003e\n\u003c/execute-bead\u003e\n","metadata":{"attempt_id":"20260507T235704-47853826","base_rev":"b612b11eb8862a1382981b90852b9c6de68cb4c2","bead_id":"ddx-60ed4dc9","bundle_path":".ddx/executions/20260507T235704-47853826","correlation_id":"ddx-60ed4dc9:20260507T235704-47853826","prompt_file":".ddx/executions/20260507T235704-47853826/prompt.md","prompt_sha":"63319ca33ad65f45504529858e706a7784cb465fc7e7be6a952eb705ab172ab9","role":"implementer","session_id":"eb-fdd71b3d","worker_id":""}}}
